OF-HAT SW Installation Intructions
**********************************

These instuctions work in Ubuntu 10.04 distribution.

HAT SW dependences:

* libusb-1.0.8
* liblabjackusb

Libusb installation:

1. Download libusb-1.0.8 sources here: 
   http://sourceforge.net/projects/libusb/files/libusb-1.0/libusb-1.0.8/

2. Extract package 

   $ tar -xvf libusb-1.0.8.tar.bz2
 
3. Read INSTALL to compile and install package or just

   $ ./configure
   $ make
   $ sudo make install


Liblabjackusb installation:

1. Download exodriver from here: https://github.com/labjack/exodriver

2. Extract exodriver 

   $ tar -zxvf labjack-exodriver-98cf1f8.tar.gz

3. Go liblabjackusb folder 

   $ cd labjack-exodriver-98cf1f8/liblabjackusb/

4. Build library 

   $ make

5. Install library

   $ sudo make install

6. Liblabjackusb needs access to the /dev/bus/usb. Run following commands in
   labjack-exodriver root folder.

   $ cd ..
   $ sudo cp 10-labjack.rules /etc/udev/rules.d
   $ sudo udevadm control --reload-rules
   
Building HAT SW

   1. Build HAT SW

   $ make

Using HAT SW to control usb and power switches.

   1. Connect HAT device to USB port and start HAT driver.
   
   $ cd src 

   $ hat_drv &

   Driver should print 'hat_drv: HAT driver started succesfully', if it has started succesfully.
   
   2. Use hat_ctrl SW to control HAT device. For example switch power output 1 on

   $ hat_ctrl -pwr1=on

   Get all parameters just type

   $ hat_ctrl

